Package: Mfactors
Title: Make factors less annoying
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Melissa", "Guzman", role=c("aut", "cre"),
  email = "guzman@zoology.ubc.ca")
Description: Factors do very funny things. Importing into R a data frame usually converts the characters into factors. Also, normally you cant bind factors. This package lets you work with factors more easily.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.0
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Imports:
    dplyr
URL: https://github.com/lmguzman/MelissaFactors
BugReports: https://github.com/lmguzman/MelissaFactors/issues
VignetteBuilder: knitr
